The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Metro | The City Diary
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                       The City Diary
                A 20-year-old resident of Udayanpally in Salt Lake died after another resident, Sankha Naskar, attacked him with an axe on Tuesday night. The victim, Samir Mondol, had tried to jump over the wooden fence around a pond at Mahishbathan to take a shortcut from Udayanpally. He was caught by Naskar, the owner of the pond, who hacked him with an axe. Samir was admitted to NRS Medical College and Hospital, but died later in the night. Naskar is absconding.    A 17-year-old boy drowned in a pond in the port area on Wednesday afternoon. The body of Wasi Ahmed was fished out after two hours. An officer of Watgunge police station said Wasi, a student of Class X, had gone to the Kidderpore-Paddapukur Square pond with his friends to take a dip.    A 55-year-old man committed suicide by hanging himself at his Asutosh Mukherjee Lane home in Howrah on Tuesday night. Rameswar Yadavs family members rushed him to the Howrah District Hospital, where he was declared dead on arrival. Yadav had been suffering from asthma for a long time, police said. A case of unnatural death has been lodged.    Sheikh Akhtar,13, a resident of Barisha in Thakurpukur was electrocuted on Wednesday evening after he touched a live wire while playing with friends. He was rushed to Vidyasagar Hospital, where he was declared dead.    Rehana Bibi, a 27-year-old resident of Birati, was brought to RG Kar Hospital with burns late on Tuesday. Doctors declared her dead on arrival. Rehana was married to a vegetable wholesaler four years back. An officer of Nimta police station said her husband and in-laws used to torture her mentally and physically. Rehanas family has filed a complaint against her husband and in-laws, who are absconding since Tuesday night.    The body of an unidentified man aged around 60 years was spotted lying on the footpath near the intersection of Marquis Street and Free School Street on Wednesday morning. There were no injury marks on the body, cops said.    An empty bus dashed an ambulance parked on APC Road on Wednesday evening. The driver of the bus, Rabiul Sheikh, 22, has been arrested on charges of negligence and rash driving.    Amalendu Dasgupta, former editor of The Statesman, died at a city nursing home on Wednesday. He was 84. He had served as the newspapers editor from 1980 to 1986. Before that, he was an assistant editor in the paper and had also served in the IAEA and All India Radio.            
